      "raw_text": "The bridge and structural iron\nworkers did not present their reso-\nluton to the trades council lastt\nnight asking that the city Of Spo-\nkane as an employer be placed on\nthe unfair list in all lines of work.\nA committee was appointed to\nbring this matter before the coun,\nGil but the committee did not call\nit up.\n\n\nGeorge Won Eschen, former bust\nness agent for the carpenters, ap\npeared before the council and stat\ned that he had been appointed by\nGovernor Hay to draft some form\nof employers liability law to be\npresented to the next session OF\nthe legislature. He asked what\nkind of liability the laboring mer\nwanted."
